  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7115.66 sitting just above the massive 7100 gamma wall (13.97B), dealers are actively selling into this strength as part of their long gamma hedging. The PIN regime and dense positive gamma concentration between 7100-7125 creates a powerful magnetic effect that should cap upside momentum and pull price back toward these key strikes. Watch 7100 as critical support - a break below triggers accelerated dealer buying into the 6800 negative gamma zone, while resistance builds heavily into the 7125-7200 corridor.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back and stick around the 7100 level.",
